### Phase 4 — Theme Scoring Matrix

After scanning, score each theme on this matrix. Only themes scoring 70+ are actionable for 10x hunting. Themes scoring 50–69 are watch-list themes — return in 12 months when the adoption curve matures.

```
THEME SCORING MATRIX (100 points total)

Secular vs Cyclical:          0–20 points
  20: Multiple secular drivers, no cyclical dependency
  15: Primarily secular, one minor cyclical element
  10: Mixed secular and cyclical
  5:  Primarily cyclical with secular narrative
  0:  Purely cyclical

TAM and Growth Rate:          0–20 points
  20: TAM >$500B, CAGR >30%
  15: TAM >$100B, CAGR >20%
  10: TAM >$50B, CAGR >15%
  5:  TAM >$20B, CAGR >10%
  0:  TAM <$20B or CAGR <10%

Adoption Curve Position:      0–20 points
  20: Early adopter phase (5–20%), inflecting upward
  15: Innovator phase (0–5%) with first PMF signals
  10: Early majority (20–40%), still room to run
  5:  Late majority (40–70%), shrinking opportunity set
  0:  Laggard phase (70%+), fully penetrated

Incumbent Vulnerability:      0–20 points
  20: Incumbents structurally unable to compete
  15: Incumbents slow to respond, 3+ year window
  10: Incumbents responding but behind
  5:  Incumbents competing actively
  0:  Theme is owned by incumbents already

Capital Formation Stage:      0–10 points
  10: Early VC formation, first IPOs appearing
  7:  Institutional capital flowing in, not yet saturated
  4:  Theme ETFs exist but not crowded
  1:  Multiple SPACs, crowded trade, retail-aware
  0:  Fully saturated, theme at peak media coverage

First Principles Validity:    0–10 points
  10: Physical or mathematical inevitability
  7:  Strong behavioral or demographic driver
  4:  Plausible but dependent on multiple assumptions
  1:  Narrative-driven, weak structural foundation
  0:  No first-principles basis

TOTAL: __/100

70–100: HIGH CONVICTION THEME — Hunt 10x stocks now
50–69:  DEVELOPING THEME — Monitor, not act
30–49:  EARLY / SPECULATIVE — Small position if any
0–29:   AVOID — Cyclical or saturated
```

